 Website Accessibility page has much information and recommendations for making a website accessible  Internet accessibility tips for vision-impaired users  Screen readers (useful to experience web pages as blind users do)  NV Access produces the free NonVisual Desktop Access (NVDA).  American Federation for the Blind has created a tutorial to learn NVDA  Freedom Scientific produces the popular but expensive JAWS available at JAWS Download . 15 minute free trial period.  Window-Eyes for Users of Microsoft Office is free.             Resources and Tools    Back to main content           Non-HTML Content     Captioning at UIC    Microsoft Word    Microsoft PowerPoint    PDF Documents    Multimedia Formats      Online Resources    Tools    Captioning at UIC                  UIC Logo        Digital Accessibility Committee       Contact   Phone: (312) 413-0886  dag@listserv.uic.edu        Social Media Accounts            UIC.edu links   UIC.edu  Academic Calendar  Athletics  Campus Directory  Disability Resources  Emergency Information  Event Calendar  Job Openings  Library  Maps  UIC Safe Mobile App  UIC Today  UI Health  Veterans Affairs        Powered by Red 2.38.0  © 2020 The Board of Trustees of the University of Illinois |  Privacy Statement    Campuses   University of Illinois System  Urbana-Champaign  Springfield      Cookie Settings                 